'''Susumu Matsushita''' (松下進 ''Matsushita Susumu'', born February 6, 1950 in [[Fussa, Tokyo]]) is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] [[manga]] artist known for his unique [[American comic book|American comic]]–influenced design. His most famous works are the designing of the mascot ''[[Neppe]]'' of ''[[Orix Buffaloes]]'', ''[[Motor Toon Grand Prix]]'', ''[[Adventure Island (video game)|Hudson's Adventure Island series]]'', ''[[Monkey Magic (TV series)|Monkey Magic]]'' and the ''[[Maximo: Ghosts to Glory]]'' concept arts.
Matsushita's illustrations have frequently appeared in [[video game magazine]]s including the creation of numerous covers for publications such as ''[[Famitsu]]'' (for which Matsushita has designed the mascot, {{nihongo|Necky|ネッキー}} the Fox<ref>Gifford, Kevin. ''[http://magweasel.com/2009/09/19/weekend-factyard-famitsufamicom-tsushin Weekend Factyard: Famitsu/Famicom Tsushin]'' MagWeasel. 19 September 2009.</ref><ref>Ashcraft, Brian. ''[http://kotaku.com/352151/gaming-magazine-totally-snubs-xbox-360 Gaming Magazine Totally Snubs Xbox 360!?] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090505131303/http://kotaku.com/352151/gaming-magazine-totally-snubs-xbox-360 |date=2009-05-05 }}''. [[Kotaku]]. 4 February 2008.</ref>). Matsushita is also responsible for creating the mascots of numerous Famitsu spinoff magazines including: *''Famitsu Bros.'' (for which Matsushita designed the mascot, Arnold) *''[[Satellaview Tsūshin]]'' (for which Matsushita designed {{nihongo|Sabi the Flying Squirrel|サビー・ザ・フライング スクウィラル}}<ref name=matsushita>''[http://www.susumumatsushita.net/press/release/pr2004_07_a.html 'Necky the Fox' 今も尚輝き続ける松下進の代表的キャラクター]''. SusumuMatsushita.net. 10 July 2004.</ref>) *''[[Famitsu PS]]'' (for which Matsushita created the {{nihongo|Penguin Bros.|ペンギン・ブラザース}}<ref name=matsushita/>) *''Game Boy Tsushin'' (for which Matsushita created the {{nihongo|Buggy the Bat|バギー・ザ・バット}}<ref name=matsushita/>) In addition to creating characters for game magazines, Matsushita has also designed mascots and characters for gaming events like [[Space World]] (Matsushita designed Lucky Rabbit and friends),<ref>''[http://www.spaceworld.co.jp/english/parkinfo/05characters.php Characters|SpaceWorld]'' SpaceWorld.co.jp. 2005.</ref> and for video games such as those in the ''[[Derby Stallion]]'' series. He also designed the mascots for the [[1994 Asian Games]] which were being hosted in [[Hiroshima]] at the time, Poppo and Cuccu.
He also drew the old Shueisha [[Business Jump]] magazine's mascot, which was a mouse.
